HEADWORD: Sweet-scented
<hw>Sweet"-scent`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a sweet
scent or smell; fragrant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sweet-scented shrub</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a
shrub of the genus <gen>Calycanthus</gen>, the flowers of which, when
crushed, have a fragrance resembling that of strawberries.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

